# VastPlan primary knowledge-graph collection policy.
#
# The primary graph is for product architecture and runtime call chains. Tests,
# fixtures and agent instruction files are deliberately kept out. Generated Go
# protobuf files remain discoverable here because the post-processor compresses
# them to contract declarations; ignoring them at scan time would also remove
# CallContext and the other protocol boundary types.

/AGENTS.md
/CLAUDE.md

*_test.go
*.test.ts
*.test.tsx
*.spec.ts
*.spec.tsx
**/testdata/
**/fixtures/
/engineering/arch/
/engineering/e2e/

# Python protobuf output does not expose useful message declarations to the
# current extractor, so it can be excluded completely.
*_pb2.py
*_pb2_grpc.py

# Graphify currently force-loads query memory. The primary-graph post-processor
# enforces this exclusion even when the scanner bypasses this rule.
/graphify-out/memory/
